## **3. XML Request Building**

Tidal uses **XML payloads** for queries:

```python name=clients/tidal_client.py url=https://github.com/CareSourceIT/ClinAuto-Clinical.Support.Services.Dashboard/blob/feature/Dashboard_AzureFunc/clients/tidal_client.py#L63-L72
xml_payload = f"""<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" ?>
<entry xmlns="http://purl.org/atom/ns#">
    <tes:JobRun.getList xmlns:tes="http://www.tidalsoftware.com/client/tesservlet">
        <selectColumns>jobid,jobname,status,statusname,actualstarttime,productiondate</selectColumns>
        <queryCondition>jobid IN('{job_id_list}') AND actualstarttime &gt;= '{start_date_str}' AND actualstarttime &lt;= '{end_date_str}'</queryCondition>
        <orderBy>jobid ASC,actualstarttime DESC</orderBy>
        <firstRow>{first_row}</firstRow>
        <numRows>{num_rows}</numRows>
    </tes:JobRun.getList>
</entry>"""
```

**XML structure:**
- Query language similar to SQL
- Filter by job IDs and date ranges
- Pagination support (`firstRow`, `numRows`)

