## **5. Response Parsing**

The API returns **XML responses** that get parsed:

```python name=clients/tidal_client.py url=https://github.com/CareSourceIT/ClinAuto-Clinical.Support.Services.Dashboard/blob/feature/Dashboard_AzureFunc/clients/tidal_client.py#L236-L282
def parse_tidal_response(xml_response: str) -> List[TidalJobRun]:
    namespaces = {
        'atom': 'http://purl.org/atom/ns#',
        'tes': 'http://www.tidalsoftware.com/client/tesservlet'
    }
    
    root = ET.fromstring(xml_response)
    entries = root.findall('.//atom:entry', namespaces)
    
    for entry in entries:
        jobrun = entry.find('tes:jobrun', namespaces)
        if jobrun is not None:
            job_id = int(job_id_elem.text)
            name = name_elem.text
            status_name = status_elem.text
            actual_start_time = datetime.fromisoformat(start_time_elem.text)
            
            results.append(TidalJobRun(
                job_id=job_id,
                name=name,
                status_name=status_name,
                actual_start_time=actual_start_time
            ))
```

**Parsing:**
- Uses `xml.etree.ElementTree` (ET)
- Extracts job ID, name, status, and timestamps
- Converts to Python dataclass models

